{"title": "Greenmantle", "description": "Greenmantle is the second of five Richard Hannay novels by John Buchan, first published in 1916 by Hodder & Stoughton, London. It is one of two Hannay novels set during the First World War, the other being Mr Standfast (1919); Hannay's first and best-known adventure, The Thirty-Nine Steps (1915), is set in the period immediately before the war started. - Hannay is called in to investigate rumours of an uprising in the Muslim world, and undertakes a perilous journey through enemy territory to meet up with his friend Sandy in Constantinople. Once there, he and his friends must thwart the Germans' plans to use religion to help them win the war, climaxing at the battle of Erzurum. (Summary from Wikipedia)", "duration": 32988, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "83", "name": "John Buchan"}], "coverArt": "https://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt/Greenmantle_1003.jpg", "copyright_year": "1916", "genres": ["Action & Adventure Fiction", "Detective Fiction", "War & Military Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Anita Roy Dobbs"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Anita Roy Dobbs"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Author's Preface & A Mission is Proposed", "readers": [1112], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/greenmantle_0709_librivox/greenmantle_01_buchan_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1347}, {"section": 2, "title": "The Gathering of the Missionaries", "readers": [688], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/greenmantle_0709_librivox/greenmantle_02_buchan_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1862}, {"section": 3, "title": "Peter Pienaar", "readers": [1112], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/greenmantle_0709_librivox/greenmantle_03_buchan_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1398}, {"section": 4, "title": "Adventures of Two Dutchmen on the Loose", "readers": [1112], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/greenmantle_0709_librivox/greenmantle_04_b